{"ts": "2026-04-24T02:02:02Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "publish-cortex-interactive-plugin-non-runner-skills-hooks-bin-utilities", "findings": ["Intent clarity rated High on '13 named skills', but research line 249 lists 15 skills for cortex-interactive — the ticket's count of 13 excludes critical-review/morning-review pending an import check. Total final count is 13 or 15 depending on the gate, not fixed at 13.", "Scope claims the hook list is bounded as '3 named hooks', but the ticket scope bullet literally reads '...plus any interactive-usable advisory hooks' — an open-ended escape-hatch. Candidate advisory hooks (cortex-skill-edit-advisor.sh, cortex-permission-audit-log.sh, cortex-output-filter.sh, cortex-cleanup-session.sh, cortex-sync-permissions.py) exist in the codebase and are not enumerated.", "Research line 53 lists cortex-tool-failure-tracker.sh as runner-required; research line 249 places the same file in cortex-interactive. The ticket silently resolves toward line 249 without naming the source contradiction. File path is also claude/hooks/cortex-tool-failure-tracker.sh, not hooks/.", "Requirements alignment asserts DR-8's project.md update is 'deferred to the epic that implements this' — but ticket 120 is a child of epic 113, not the epic itself, and decomposed.md does not assign the project.md rewrite to any specific child ticket (120, 121, 122, 124 are all enumerated without that deliverable).", "Storage policy uses ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA} listed as one of four concrete bounding mechanisms, but the ticket says 'any Python code lives in the CLI tier' and the bullet's phrasing 'any cache/venv state that must survive' is conditional — no concrete state is named. Treats optional policy guidance as a hard boundary.", "Out-of-scope bullet excludes '#117 symlink retirement' but #117 is already complete per recent commits — the exclusion is historical/redundant. More importantly no exclusion is stated for CLI-tier work (cortex setup, cortex init, 